def: One who takes part in a folkmote, or local court. [Obs.]Milton.
A colorless, mobile, inflammable liquid, C2H5.NH2, veryvolatile and with an ammoniacal odor. It is a strong base, and is aderivative of ammonia. Called also ethyl carbamine, and amido ethane.
That which is furnished as a specimen; a sample; a supply.[Obs.] Greene.
A perennial herb (Gypsophila Struthium) the root of which isused in Spain as a substitute for soap.
A gay seducer of women; a libertine.
To make sport contempt or in jest; to speak in a scornful orjeering manner.When thou mockest, shall no man make thee ashamed Job xi. 3.She had mocked at his proposal. Froude.
Having the quality of sticking to a surface; adhesive; gluey;viscous; viscid; glutinous; tenacious.Herbs which last longest are those of strong smell, and with a stickystalk. Bacon.
One of a tribe of tortoises, including the terrapins, etc., inwhich the head and neck can be withdrawn.
